  "doc_id": "47499",
  "text": "Culturing and transfection of BHK and HepG2 cells were carried out as described previously [CITATION_1] . To detect WHsAg and WHcAg, immunofluorescence staining was performed with monoclonal mouse anti-WHpreS [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] or anti-WHcAg antibodies [CITATION_4] . The antiWHpreS antibody recognizes the middle WHsAg that contains the major WHsAg as a domain. The expression of EGFP by the WHx-EGFP fusion was determined by direct observation and photography under a fluorescence microscope with an excitation wavelength of 490 nm.",
